result.execSummary:
The defendant Zachary Nathan Davis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class A felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).
  • Armed Robbery with Use of Force [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).
  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
To pay restitution in an amount to be determined.  State to provide final restitution amount within 30 days; defense has 30 days after receipt to request a restitution hearing.

25% of any income earned in prison to be applied to restitution.
Sentenced to life in prison.  Not eligible for release to extended supervision.
